script.name: plugin.planets.init
script.sourceplaintext:
$page.id = get global variable: name='pageid.guilds'
$data = table alloc
$tProduction = table alloc $data['production'] = $tProduction
$read.file = read types file lines: filename='TProduction' if $read.file $version = null $i = 0 $size = size of array $read.file while $i < $size $line = $read.file[$i] inc $i = $split = split string: $line separator=';' $line.size = size of array $split if is datatype[ $version ] == DATATYPE_NULL if $line.size >= 2 $version = $split[0] $entries = $split[1] $entries = string $entries to integer $version = string $version to integer end else if $line.size >= 4 $ware = $split[0] $ware = get ware from subtype name $ware if $ware $products = $split[1] $products = string $products to integer $product.time = $split[2] $product.time = string $product.time to integer $resource.count = $split[3] $resource.count = string $resource.count to integer $remaining = ( $line.size - 4 ) / 2
$tProduct = table alloc $tProduction[$ware] = $tProduct $tResources = table alloc $tProduct['count'] = $products $tProduct['time'] = $product.time $tResources = table alloc $tProduct['resources'] = $tResources
if $remaining >= $resource.count $pos = 4 while $resource.count dec $resource.count = $resource = $split[$pos] $resource = get ware from subtype name $resource inc $pos = $r.count = $split[$pos] $r.count = string $r.count to integer inc $pos = if $resource AND $r.count > 0 $tResources[$resource] = $r.count end end end end end end end end
* Read the planets data from a types file $read.file = read types file lines: filename='TPlanetEcon' if $read.file $version = null $i = 0 $size = size of array $read.file while $i < $size $line = $read.file[$i] inc $i = $split = split string: $line separator=';' $line.size = size of array $split if is datatype[ $version ] == DATATYPE_NULL if $line.size >= 2 $version = $split[0] $entries = $split[1] $entries = string $entries to integer $version = string $version to integer end else if $line.size >= 8
$sec.x = $split[0] $sec.x = string $sec.x to integer $sec.y = $split[1] $sec.y = string $sec.y to integer $sector = get sector from universe index: x=$sec.x, y=$sec.y if $sector -> exists $old.sector = $data[$sector] skip if $old.sector $old.sector = table alloc $tSector = table alloc $data[$sector] = $tSector $tProducts = table alloc $tSector['production'] = $tProducts $tRawProducts = table alloc $tSector['raw.production'] = $tRawProducts $tConsumtion = table alloc $tSector['consumtion'] = $tConsumtion
$enabled = $split[2] $enabled = string $enabled to integer $tSector['enabled'] = $enabled *write to player logbook: printf: type=[Log.Debug], fmt=null, null, null, null, null, null
$include.pop = $split[3] $include.pop = string $include.pop to integer if $include.pop > 0 AND $include.pop < 10 $sector ->set sector population: $include.pop $tSector['pop'] = [TRUE] else $tSector['pop'] = [FALSE] end
$value = $split[4] $value = string $value to integer if not $old.sector['prosperity'] $tSector['prosperity'] = $value $tSector['prosperity.level'] = 5000 end
$value = $split[5] $value = string $value to integer $tSector['max.prosperity'] = $value
$arr = create new array, arguments='production', 'consumtion', 'raw.production', null, null $arr.size = size of array $arr
$pos = 6 $j = 0 while $j < $arr.size $use.value = $arr[$j] inc $j = do if $old.sector $old.table = $old.sector[$use.value] $use.table = $tSector[$use.value]
$w.count = $split[$pos] $w.count = string $w.count to integer inc $pos =
while $w.count dec $w.count = $value = $split[$pos] $ware = get ware from subtype name $value inc $pos = $value = $split[$pos] $prosperity.level = string $value to integer inc $pos = $value = $split[$pos] $product.count = string $value to integer inc $pos = $value = $split[$pos] $product.time = string $value to integer inc $pos =
if $ware $table = table alloc if $old.table $table = $old.table[$ware] skip if $table $table = table alloc end $use.table[$ware] = $table $table['prosperity'] = $prosperity.level if $product.count AND $product.count $table['count'] = $product.count $table['time'] = $product.time end end end end end end end end end
set global variable: name='planets.data' value=$data return null

comment.var: Read the planets data from a types file

line.text: get sector from universe index: x=

line.comment: *write to player logbook: printf: type=[Log.Debug], fmt=null, null, null, null, null, null

sval.val: Read the planets data from a types file
